@realmoney My Question of the Day "Common sense is not too common." - Voltaire As previously mentioned, six months ago the Fed was looking at and the market was anticipating three interest rate hikes. Today, three interest rate reductions are expected. Again, working off of my

opener today and last week's column, The Fed is Pushing on a String - does anyone seriously think that a two year U.S. note yielding less than 1.90% is a headwind or obstacle to economic growth, and that a 10 year U.S. note yielding 2.14% restricts capital spending or the

decision of an entrepreneur to start/build a business? As the wise man said, common sense is not too common. And, as Grandma Koufax used to say, "Dougie, meshuganah is trump." (Meaning in Yiddish, that craziness is three-fold). @jimcramer @SquawkCNBC @cnbcfastmoney @lizclaman
